N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 ยง 331.6 - Advertising

State Regulations

All rules and procedures of the chair relating to
advertising by a physician as set forth in section
325-1.16
of this Title are made
applicable to psychologists, to the extent that they are not inconsistent with
the provisions of section
13-m
of the Workers' Compensation Law and the other provisions duly promulgated
thereunder. Notes
